<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="761" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6604: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-24T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                            1920—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your 137, March 18, 6 p.m. Department prefers that you should not
                                participate in any conference with your colleagues looking to an
                                arrangement for peace negotiations between Bolsheviki and
                                Latvia.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>